{"id":"1304.1965","submitter":"Holger Fehske","authors":"B. Zenker, H. Fehske, H. Beck, C. Monney, and A. R. Bishop","title":"Chiral charge order in 1$T$-TiSe$_2$: importance of lattice degrees of\n  freedom","comments":"13 pages, 11 figures, revised and extended version","journal-ref":"Phys. Rev. B 88, 075138 (2013)","doi":"10.1103/PhysRevB.88.075138","report-no":null,"categories":"cond-mat.str-el","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We address the question of the origin of the recently discovered chiral\nproperty of the charge-density-wave phase in 1$T$-TiSe$_2$ which so far lacks a\nmicroscopic understanding. We argue that the lattice degrees of freedom seems\nto be crucial for this novel phenomenon. We motivate a theoretical model that\ntakes into account one valence and three conduction bands, a strongly screened\nCoulomb interaction between the electrons, as well as the coupling of the\nelectrons to a transverse optical phonon mode. The Falicov-Kimball model\nextended in this way possesses a charge-density-wave state at low temperatures,\nwhich is accompanied by a periodic lattice distortion. The charge ordering is\ndriven by a lattice deformation and electron-hole pairing (excitonic)\ninstability in combination. We show that both electron-phonon interaction and\nphonon-phonon interaction must be taken into account at least up to quartic\norder in the lattice displacement to achieve a stable chiral charge order. The\nchiral property is exhibited in the ionic displacements. Furthermore, we\nprovide the ground-state phase diagram of the model and give an estimate of the\nelectron-electron and electron-phonon interaction constants for 1$T$-TiSe$_2$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 7 Apr 2013 07:40:15 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 24 Aug 2013 08:54:14 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-15"}
